l2tpGlobUdpPort.name: l2tpGlobUdpPort
l2tpGlobUdpPort.description: The UDP port which is monitored by L2TP for tunnel establishment requests received from remote hosts.

l2tpGlobPortUsage.name: l2tpGlobPortUsage
l2tpGlobPortUsage.description: This object specifies whether L2TP uses only one UDP port (which number is defined by l2tpGlobUdpPort), or if it allocates a new available port, to send messages to the remote equipment. Choosing 'single' makes it sometimes easier to process L2TP through NAT since L2TP traffic can be classified based on the UDP port number. Choosing 'floating' selects the behavior which is recommended in RFC2331. Possible values: single(1), -- L2TP uses the UDP port defined by l2tpGlobUdpPort -- to send messages to the remote equipment. floating(2) -- L2TP allocates a new port to send messages to -- the remote equipment (default).

l2tpTunnelProfileTable.name: l2tpTunnelProfileTable
l2tpTunnelProfileTable.description: This table contains profile information for L2TP tunnels.

l2tpTunnelProfileIndex.name: l2tpTunnelProfileIndex
l2tpTunnelProfileIndex.description: The unique index for this entry.

l2tpTunnelProfileName.name: l2tpTunnelProfileName
l2tpTunnelProfileName.description: The friendly name for this entry.

l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteIpAddress.name: l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteIpAddress
l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteIpAddress.description: The main remote IP address for the tunnel. Only meaningful in LAC mode. If l2tpTunnelProfileRadiusAssignment is set to 'enabled', this object is ignored and the L2TP daemon will ask the Radius daemon to send a request for the main and backup remote IP addresses.

l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteIpAddressBackup.name: l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteIpAddressBackup
l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteIpAddressBackup.description: The backup remote IP address for the tunnel. Only meaningful in LAC mode. If l2tpTunnelProfileRadiusAssignment is set to 'enabled', this object is ignored and the L2TP daemon will ask the Radius daemon to send a request for the main and backup remote IP addresses.

l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteUdpPort.name: l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteUdpPort
l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteUdpPort.description: The remote UDP port number for the tunnel. Only meaningful in LAC mode.

l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteHostname.name: l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteHostname
l2tpTunnelProfileRemoteHostname.description: The name of the remote host. Use an empty string for default profile.

l2tpTunnelProfileLocalIpAddress.name: l2tpTunnelProfileLocalIpAddress
l2tpTunnelProfileLocalIpAddress.description: The local IP address for the tunnel. If this value is set to 0, the IP address of the egress interface will be used in outgoing L2TP packets.

l2tpTunnelProfileLocalUdpPort.name: l2tpTunnelProfileLocalUdpPort
l2tpTunnelProfileLocalUdpPort.description: The local UDP port number for the tunnel. Only meaningful in LAC mode. If this value is set to 0 (zero), the port number is allocated dynamically.

l2tpTunnelProfileLocalHostname.name: l2tpTunnelProfileLocalHostname
l2tpTunnelProfileLocalHostname.description: The name of the local host.

l2tpTunnelProfilePassword.name: l2tpTunnelProfilePassword
l2tpTunnelProfilePassword.description: The password used for tunnel authentication.

l2tpTunnelProfileReceiveWindowSize.name: l2tpTunnelProfileReceiveWindowSize
l2tpTunnelProfileReceiveWindowSize.description: The received window size used by L2TP on the local side of this tunnel. Currently, the only supported value is 1.

l2tpTunnelProfileHelloInterval.name: l2tpTunnelProfileHelloInterval
l2tpTunnelProfileHelloInterval.description: The interval in seconds between two consecutive hello requests sent by L2TP during the tunnel life. If this object is set to 0 (zero), no hello requests are sent by L2TP on this tunnel.

l2tpTunnelProfileSessionDataSequencing.name: l2tpTunnelProfileSessionDataSequencing
l2tpTunnelProfileSessionDataSequencing.description: This object specifies if sequence numbers are used on the data channel of sessions supported by this tunnel. Additionally, if this object is set to delete (1), the entry is marked for discard.

l2tpTunnelProfileMinRetryTime.name: l2tpTunnelProfileMinRetryTime
l2tpTunnelProfileMinRetryTime.description: The initial interval in seconds between two consecutive attempts to send an L2TP control packet. The value of this interval is doubled with each new attempt, until the maximum value defined in l2tpTunnelProfileMaxRetryTime is reached.

l2tpTunnelProfileMaxRetryTime.name: l2tpTunnelProfileMaxRetryTime
l2tpTunnelProfileMaxRetryTime.description: The maximum interval in seconds between two consecutive attempts to send an L2TP control packet.

l2tpTunnelProfileMaxRetries.name: l2tpTunnelProfileMaxRetries
l2tpTunnelProfileMaxRetries.description: The maximum number of retries to send an L2TP control packet. The total number of attempts will be one more than this value.

l2tpTunnelProfileRadiusAssignment.name: l2tpTunnelProfileRadiusAssignment
l2tpTunnelProfileRadiusAssignment.description: This object enables/disables the use of Radius for requesting main and backup remote IP addresses. Only meaningful in LAC mode.

l2tpTunnelProfileRadiusGroupId.name: l2tpTunnelProfileRadiusGroupId
l2tpTunnelProfileRadiusGroupId.description: Determines the logical RADIUS server group to be addressed for sending the RADIUS Access-Request messages. Only meaningful in LAC mode. See also radiusSrvGroupId.

l2tpTunnelPassword.description: The password used for tunnel authentication.

l2tpTunnelHelloInterval.description: The interval in seconds between two consecutive hello requests sent by L2TP during the tunnel life. If this object is set to 0 (zero), no hello requests are sent by L2TP on this tunnel.

l2tpTunnelSessionDataSequencing.name: l2tpTunnelSessionDataSequencing
l2tpTunnelSessionDataSequencing.description: This object specifies if sequence numbers are used on the data channel of sessions supported by this tunnel.

l2tpTunnelMinRetryTime.name: l2tpTunnelMinRetryTime
l2tpTunnelMinRetryTime.description: The initial interval in seconds between two consecutive attempts to send an L2TP control packet. The value of this interval is doubled with each new attempt, until the maximum value defined in l2tpTunnelProfileMaxRetryTime is reached.

l2tpTunnelMaxRetryTime.name: l2tpTunnelMaxRetryTime
l2tpTunnelMaxRetryTime.description: The maximum interval in seconds between two consecutive attempts to send an L2TP control packet.

l2tpTunnelMaxRetries.name: l2tpTunnelMaxRetries
l2tpTunnelMaxRetries.description: The maximum number of retries to send an L2TP control packet. The total number of attempts will be one more than this value.

l2tpTunnelState.name: l2tpTunnelState
l2tpTunnelState.description: The current state of the tunnel as specified in RFC2661. Selecting shutdown(5) value results in tunnel hangup. Any other value is ignored.
